<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1880,2013]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="275" pageId="1" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,1952,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="274">Re-description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[390,687,1952,1977]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="274">Male. General coloration.</emphasis>
Uniformly green with some brown to black markings at posterior end of tegmina (
<figureCitation box="[339,405,1988,2013]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1711,1733]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,409,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[150,1436,409,1690]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Morphological details of male Philoscirtus species. A, C, E. P. cordipennis B, D, F. P. viridulus n. sp.. A, B. Lateral view on abdomen and head C, D. Dorsal view on tegmina, pronotum and head. E, F. Dorsal view on subgenital plate. Scale bars: 4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233460/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="274">
Fig. 
<number box="[392,405,1989,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="274" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C) and black spots at posterior end medially on tergites 
<number box="[1046,1091,1988,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="274" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7</number>
. 
<emphasis box="[1103,1333,1988,2013]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="274">Head and antennae.</emphasis>
Antenna very long, 
<quantity box="[275,344,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="2" pageNumber="275" unit="cm" value="11.0">11 cm</quantity>
and thus about 
<number box="[529,571,152,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="275" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
times as long as body length. 
<bibRefCitation box="[922,1122,152,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="275" refString="La Baume, W. (1911) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der aethiopischen Orthopteren. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung, 72, 308 - 326." type="journal article">
La Baume (
<number box="[1057,1114,152,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="275" value="1911.0">1911</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
records a male with 
<quantity box="[1365,1436,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="275" unit="cm" value="13.0">13 cm</quantity>
long antennae collected at Amani by Vosseler. 
<emphasis box="[679,768,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="275">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotum up-curved at posterior margin, very rugose (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1711,1733]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,409,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[150,1436,409,1690]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Morphological details of male Philoscirtus species. A, C, E. P. cordipennis B, D, F. P. viridulus n. sp.. A, B. Lateral view on abdomen and head C, D. Dorsal view on tegmina, pronotum and head. E, F. Dorsal view on subgenital plate. Scale bars: 4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233460/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="275">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,164,224,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="275" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A, C). Fore femora armed with 
<number box="[532,574,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="275" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
inner and 
<number box="[700,742,224,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="275" value="0.5" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.0">0–1</number>
outer stout short spines, marked brown to black at posterior outer side; posterior ends of femora with reddish pair of spurs. 
<emphasis box="[857,917,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="275">Legs.</emphasis>
All femora slightly laterally compressed. Mid femora with 
<number box="[293,335,296,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="275" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
stout spines at posterior part, also with a pair of stout spurs. 
<collectingCountry box="[1012,1068,295,320]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="275">Hind</collectingCountry>
femora with numerous stout and acute brown spines and a pair of stout spurs at lunules. 
<emphasis box="[811,925,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="275">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Cerci green, short and rather stout, slightly inwardly curved. Subgenital plate elongated with slender middle part and expanded posterior part. Posterior part brown, triangularly incised, thus forming a fork with pointed tips (
<figureCitation box="[895,961,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1711,1733]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,409,1688]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[150,1436,409,1690]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Morphological details of male Philoscirtus species. A, C, E. P. cordipennis B, D, F. P. viridulus n. sp.. A, B. Lateral view on abdomen and head C, D. Dorsal view on tegmina, pronotum and head. E, F. Dorsal view on subgenital plate. Scale bars: 4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233460/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="275">
Fig. 
<number box="[947,961,404,428]" pageId="2" pageNumber="275" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
E). With minute styli.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
